Agropyron desertorum

   [2921.jpg]
    Authority   (Fischer ex Link) Schultes
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names standard crested wheatgrass
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 2921

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A variable deep rooted bunchgrass reaching a height
   of 50-100 cm. USES Can be used for regrassing abandoned and depleted
   cropland. It is a valuable forage grass. KILLING T Frost tolerant.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Long-lived perennial, with a economical life of 20-35 years. COMMON
   NAMES
   Crested wheatgrass (Standard), Standard crested wheatgrass. FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Triticum desertorum. Crested wheatgrass is
   considered native of Eurasia. In the subtropics, it is adapted to
   elevations between 1500-2800 m. It is drought hardy.

   Sources
   SOURCES (A. desertorum (Fesch. ex Link) Schult.)
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 80 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Heath M 1985 pp 170 [RAIN, KTMP, DEP, TEXT, SAL, USE]
   Kernick M 1978 pp 35-61 [DEP, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, FER, PH]
   Duke J 1975 pp 5 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Shing T 1992 pp 305 [KTMP, TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, LIG]

